11/08/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Authorities announced on Monday (August 10th) the launch of a tender procedure for Pristina's international airport.
Companies interested in bidding have until September 23rd to register.
The Ministry of Transport said in a statement that it is seeking a private investor to build a new terminal, control tower, hangar and a parking area in exchange for running the airport for 20 years.
The winner will be announced by year's end.
(Reuters, AP - 10/08/09)
